C. Financial SME Knowledge Development
To strengthen my financial domain expertise and contextual understanding of regulatory frameworks:

- IFRS 17 Certification:
  Completed a six-month course on IFRS 17, covering principles of insurance contract measurement, risk adjustment, and financial reporting for insurance entities.
  Gained a strong grasp of:
  - Key measurement models (Building Block Approach, PAA, and VFA)
  - Recognition and presentation of insurance liabilities
  - Disclosure and actuarial implications under the new accounting standard

- Practical Relevance:
  This learning has enriched my ability to interpret financial data, particularly around cash flow projections, valuation adjustments, and earnings pattern analysis, and to contextualize analytical outputs within regulatory frameworks.
  It also enables better collaboration with stakeholders across risk and finance who work on IFRS-driven or model-based financial analyses.

